00:26:43.240 --> 00:26:47.850
Okay, so we've added some great
structure and color,

00:26:47.850 --> 00:26:49.400
embellishments and fonts.

00:26:49.400 --> 00:26:51.640
Let's now enhance our book.

00:26:51.750 --> 00:26:53.480
Let's add content to the book.

00:26:53.910 --> 00:26:55.160
And these are EPUBs.

00:26:55.160 --> 00:26:56.480
These are ebooks after all.

00:26:56.480 --> 00:27:00.160
We can break out of the physical
book metaphor and go beyond.

00:27:00.160 --> 00:27:08.440
One really great method to push the
book is utilizing nonlinear documents.

00:27:08.520 --> 00:27:15.720
Nonlinear documents are part of the
EPUB spec and it's a method for you to

00:27:16.060 --> 00:27:19.310
embed supplementary content in your book.

00:27:19.370 --> 00:27:23.560
It's great for embedding PDFs, charts,
quiz answers,

00:27:23.560 --> 00:27:29.400
because the reader can never flip
a page to access this content.

00:27:29.400 --> 00:27:32.810
You, the developer,
need to provide a link

00:27:33.030 --> 00:27:34.720
for them to get there.

00:27:35.130 --> 00:27:39.560
And when that link is included,
when that link is triggered,

00:27:39.560 --> 00:27:44.060
iBooks will open this nonlinear
document into a new web view

00:27:44.060 --> 00:27:46.030
that overlays your book.

00:27:46.330 --> 00:27:49.920
This web view contains an
HTML content in your book.

00:27:50.080 --> 00:27:53.130
That means all of the text
in there is searchable,

00:27:53.130 --> 00:27:54.190
selectable.

00:27:54.680 --> 00:27:56.400
This is an HTML made chart.

00:27:56.400 --> 00:27:56.440
And

00:27:58.140 --> 00:28:03.510
And because it's not subject to the
paginated environment of iBooks,

00:28:03.510 --> 00:28:08.240
that content can be panned and zoomed
in and it maintains its formatting.

00:28:08.400 --> 00:28:11.690
So let me show you how
to make one of these.

00:28:13.040 --> 00:28:15.500
Here is our code with our chart.

00:28:15.500 --> 00:28:21.030
So this is an image of our chart
in line between our paragraphs.

00:28:21.160 --> 00:28:26.100
You're going to add an anchor tag that
points to the new nonlinear document.

00:28:26.100 --> 00:28:29.260
So in this case we're
calling it chart.xhtml.

00:28:29.390 --> 00:28:33.000
So now you need to make
that new nonlinear document.

00:28:33.080 --> 00:28:34.250
Here's our new document.

00:28:34.400 --> 00:28:37.760
We've put in a table there
to represent our chart.

00:28:37.800 --> 00:28:41.560
But because you're making
a new content document,

00:28:41.630 --> 00:28:45.660
you must also include that
content document in the spine.

00:28:45.820 --> 00:28:47.000
So this is the spine.

00:28:47.110 --> 00:28:50.920
We're adding a new item called chart.

00:28:50.940 --> 00:28:52.670
And the magic there is in gold.

00:28:52.790 --> 00:28:55.150
And that's the linear attribute.

00:28:55.290 --> 00:28:57.280
And we've set it to no.

00:28:57.430 --> 00:29:01.260
This is what tells iBooks, hey,
a reader should never be able

00:29:01.350 --> 00:29:03.260
to flip to get to this document.

00:29:03.270 --> 00:29:09.500
And if this document is reached by
through a link that you have provided,

00:29:09.530 --> 00:29:12.140
iBooks should open it in a new web view.

00:29:12.170 --> 00:29:13.900
So let's run through this one more time.

00:29:13.980 --> 00:29:17.280
There's our book, an image of our chart.

00:29:17.280 --> 00:29:20.770
That chart is linked to
a nonlinear document.

00:29:20.900 --> 00:29:25.900
So when that chart is selected,
it opens into a new web view where

00:29:25.980 --> 00:29:28.450
the reader can pan and zoom in.

00:29:29.210 --> 00:29:31.200
Non-linear documents are really useful.

00:29:31.200 --> 00:29:34.260
I think once you start playing with them,
you'll actually find a lot of

00:29:34.260 --> 00:29:38.070
uses for them and they're a really
great way of enhancing your book.

00:29:38.100 --> 00:29:43.080
One other really good way of enhancing
your book is to embed audio and

00:29:43.080 --> 00:29:48.500
video and iBooks makes this really
easy because it's all standard HTML.

00:29:48.740 --> 00:29:52.100
You're going to use the HTML5
video and audio elements.

00:29:52.100 --> 00:29:54.510
I want to walk through
them here really quickly.

00:29:54.640 --> 00:29:57.360
You can see that they're
very similar to each other.

00:29:57.400 --> 00:30:00.770
They both contain a source
URL that points to the media

00:30:00.770 --> 00:30:02.490
within your EPUB bundle.

00:30:02.710 --> 00:30:05.600
They both also contain
the controls attribute.

00:30:05.600 --> 00:30:09.850
This is the default controls but you
do need to provide it because this

00:30:09.850 --> 00:30:16.070
is what allows your user to scrub,
play and pause your media.

00:30:16.310 --> 00:30:21.700
The video element is unique
because it contains a poster image.

00:30:21.900 --> 00:30:26.740
That poster image is the image that
displays in line in your paragraphs.

00:30:26.760 --> 00:30:28.780
In this case, you can see it's of a cat.

00:30:28.880 --> 00:30:33.140
Its purpose is to entice the
reader to want to play your video.

00:30:33.280 --> 00:30:35.790
This is an excellent choice
because we all know everyone

00:30:35.790 --> 00:30:37.710
likes watching videos of cats.

00:30:37.800 --> 00:30:42.800
And optionally,
you can also include the dimensions.

00:30:42.800 --> 00:30:45.800
You don't need to include dimensions.

00:30:45.800 --> 00:30:46.800
iBooks has default.

00:30:46.800 --> 00:30:50.790
iBooks will also ensure that your video
never flows over the side of a page.

00:30:50.800 --> 00:30:57.080
The audio and video elements are
a really good example of how HTML,

00:30:57.110 --> 00:31:04.030
when paired with EPUB and CSS,
really are the embodiment and power

00:31:04.030 --> 00:31:07.720
of web technology in the flowing book.

00:31:07.800 --> 00:31:13.010
But even more impressive is the
sheer precision that's possible with

00:31:13.050 --> 00:31:15.800
web technology in the fixed book.

